Key Match Events: Mohamed Bayo scored a last-minute goal in the eighth minute of stoppage time to secure a 1-0 victory for Guinea.
Equatorial Guinea missed a penalty after Iban Salvador was fouled in the penalty area.
Federico Bikoro of Equatorial Guinea was sent off in the 55th minute for a high-foot tackle on Mohamed Bayo.
Post-Match Reflections: Guinea ended a long sequence of losing in the AFCON knockout stages.
Equatorial Guinea's fairytale run ended after finishing ahead of hosts Ivory Coast and Nigeria in Group A.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at Alassane Ouattara Olympic Stadium with an attendance of 36,340.
Guinea will meet the winner of the Democratic Republic of Congo vs Egypt match in the quarterfinals.
